, warriors, and commoners expressed their competing concerns and ambitions during a chaotic period in Japanese history, as well as their shifting understandings of the tale itself. By translating these creative responses from an era of uncertainty and turmoil, Celebrating Sorrow shows the richness and enduring relevance of Japanese classical and medieval literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJapanese literaturey1185-1600xHistory and criticism. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Japanese.2bisacsh  ahistory of the tale of sagoromo, tributes to the tale of sagoromo, medieval adaptations of heian literature, warriors and heian literature, heian tales and renga.1 aD’Etcheverry, Charo B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501764790?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501764790423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501764790/original  a978-3-11-075182-6  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-all